gitCommit.subject: Migration guide for Registry v2 to v3 (#7396)
gitCommit.body:
Migration guide for Registry v2 to v3 (#7396)

* docs: comprehensive migration guide for Registry v2 to v3

This commit adds a comprehensive migration guide for migrating from
Apicurio Registry 2.x to 3.x, including:

- Detailed overview of changes in Registry 3.x (data model, API, storage)
- Two migration approaches: minimal downtime and maintenance window
- Phase-based workflow with validation checkpoints
- Data migration procedures using export/import APIs
- Client application migration guidance (SerDes, SDKs, REST API)
- Configuration property mapping (v2 to v3)
- KafkaSQL storage changes and topic configuration
- UI architectural changes and deployment options
- Troubleshooting guide for common issues

Adds migration scripts:
- apicurio-capture-metrics.sh - Captures baseline metrics
- apicurio-export-registry-data.sh - Exports v2 registry data
- apicurio-import-registry-data.sh - Imports data into v3
- apicurio-verify-registry-version.sh - Verifies registry health
- apicurio-verify-v3-api-features.sh - Tests v3 API features

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

* docs: address PR review feedback

- Remove individual script links from bullet points
- Change folder link to point to 3.1.x branch instead of main

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

---------

Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
